post_text: Ready4K Announcement - If you have a child in grades pre-k through 4th grade, on Friday, April 24, 2020, you will be invited via text messaging to participate in a program called Ready4K. Ready4K will send you one text message every Monday, Wednesday, and Friday. These messages will share tips and ideas on how to help your child at home with their academic, social and emotional development. This is a free service provided by Ready4K for our families. Please feel free to opt out of these text messages at any point. Thank you!

Information regarding Kindergarten Registration will go live on the Waynesboro Area School District Webpage at the beginning of February.

March 18, 2019 - Mowrey Elementary
March 19, 2019 - Hooverville Elementary
March 20, 2019 - Summitview Elementary
March 21, 2019 - Fairview Elementary
March 22, 2019 - Fairview Elementary & Late Registrants

We hope to see you there!

FREE HOT DOGS ARE BACK!!!

To KICK OFF the school year we are hosting our 7th annual community night, this Friday evening at the stadium, and yes FREE HOT DOGS and POTATO ROLLS are back thanks to Martin's and Martin's Potato Rolls.

We will have games, candy, face painting, and the opportunity to test your skills with our athletes and coaches on the turf field at Buchanan Auto Park Stadium.

The on field events will last from 5PM to 6PM. The band and cheerleaders will showcase their halftime performances shortly after 6PM and we will introduce our High School, Middle School, and Youth Athletic teams as they run out through the tunnel to conclude the evening.

THE EVENT IS FREE AND OPEN TO EVERYONE.

So come on out to Waynesboro Area Senior High School starting at 5PM tonight Friday, August 17, 2018 for a great community night with FREE HOT DOGS AND DRINKS.

LET'S GO BORO

Waynesboro Area Middle School
January 17, 2018 at 6:05 PM ·

It is hard to believe, but planning has begun for the 2018-2019 school year! On January 25th, WASHS will hold Educational Planning Night at 6:30 PM. If your child is entering 9th grade in 2018-2019, this is a valuable opportunity to learn about programs offered at WASHS.

During Educational Planning Night for 8th, 9th, 10th, and 11th grade (at WASHS on January 25, 2018), WASD Special Education Department is holding a coinciding transition event. This event will be in the hallway located by the Cafeteria. The transition event is themed The Next Step for Families and will take place from 6:30-8:00 p.m..

Mowrey Elementary School
January 14, 2018 at 7:53 PM ·

The 2018-19 school year will bring new opportunities for our kindergarten students. As part of our comprehensive kindergarten program, students will participate in social play daily. The kindergarten team is looking for slightly used items for the students to use during this time. If you are willing to donate any of the following items, please drop them off at Mowrey. Thank you!

• Kitchen center (and items for in a kitchen center- plastic
food, plates, cups…)
• Tool center (plastic hammers, screwdrivers…)
• Building items (Legos, waffle blocks, Magna-tiles, wood
blocks)
• Play-Doh creation sets
• Puppets
• Cars, trucks, trains
• Dolls
• Cash registers
• Play houses (tree house, doll house)
• Plastic animals (farm and zoo sets)
